President Joe Biden and Vice President Kamala Harris met with the Congressional Black Caucus (CBC) to discuss important topics such as economic empowerment, voting rights, the George Floyd Justice in Policing Act, and how the American Jobs Plan will address racial equity and historical inequities. They shared their vision of making a generational investment in racial justice through job opportunities, climate justice, clean water, equitable transportation, affordable housing, and support for caregivers. The President also emphasized his commitment to diversity in appointments and nominations, including judicial candidates. This meeting highlights the ongoing partnership between the President, Vice President, and the CBC, as well as the administration's dedication to their legislative goals and priorities.